post_text:
Hershey Patrons,

This is a message from the Hershey Administration. Due to the increase of COVID-19 activity in our region we have decided to postpone the start of school for students by one week. Our starting date will now be August 24, 2020. Monday, August 24th will still be a half day of school. Doors will open at 7:50 and school will dismiss at 11:30. We look forward to seeing our students on August 24th. Please continue to monitor the school website and social media for any further information. If you need to update your contact information with the school, please call the office at 368-5575.

Thank you.

post_text:
Hershey Public Schools are taking a census of children living in the school district from birth though age 21. Any baby born though June 30th of the current year will be included for the current year's census. The census is used for reporting a count of all children to the State of Nebraska by ages and is also used by the district for program planning.

If your children are already attending school here, we have that information, but if you have younger children not in the school system, we need this information. This if for all students living in the district even if you do not attend school at Hershey Public Schools. Please complete the form below.

If you have any questions please contact Diana Connell at Hershey Public Schools 308-368-5573 or email: diana.connell@hpspanthers.org

bit.ly/2020HersheyCensus

JH SPARKLERS

We are working on preparing for Hershey‚Äôs junior high dance team Sparklers tryouts ü§ó

Under current conditions we are taking preparation to possibly be able to do this remotely through technology. We do not have a date set yet, but we are wanting to get the word out to have anyone that may be interested in trying out for the team. We understand this is not ideal, and will do our best to help prepare and accommodate the girls anyway we can. The big thing now is getting word out to those girls interested so they can be sure and have any and all future updates about tryouts.

If interested or have any questions, please contact Tonia McConnell at (308)660-0941 and we will had you to the list.

shared_text:
Celebrate Together While Apart
April 7 at 10:36 AM ¬∑

Egg Decorating Contest! Though many Easter activities have been canceled, we can still decorate eggs together from the safety of our homes. To participate, decorate an egg using any materials you can find at home. Decorations are not limited to dying. Try gluing, painting, adding jewels, etc. If you do not have eggs or typical decorating materials please do not buy them, be creative and make your own! Photograph your best egg and post it to the Celebrate Together While Apart Facebook page including the participant‚Äôs name/nickname and age category (Junior: 6 and under, Intermediate: 7-12, Senior: 13-18, Adult: over 18) in the post. Multiple posts may be made by one account (parents posting for kids, etc.) so long as different names are given. Only one entry per person and one egg per entry allowed. Entries must be posted by 11:59 p.m. CDT on April 13th. Winners will be picked from each category based on creativity, uniqueness, design, effective use of materials, and quality of work. Winners will be announced on April 15th.

post_text:
HERSHEY PUBLIC SCHOOLS
PRESCHOOL REGISTRATION/ORIENTATION NIGHT

Preschool registration and orientation for the 2020-2021 preschool class at Hershey Elementary will take place on Monday, March 23 from 6:00 PM to 7:00 PM in the school cafeteria. Please enter through the double doors on the south side of the building.

Eligibility for the program means a child will be four (4) years of age by July 31, 2020. Students residing in the Hershey district will be enrolled first, then siblings of option students will be considered if room is available.

Parents and students will meet the principal and the preschool teacher to discuss the first year of school and fill out necessary enrollment forms. Parents are asked to bring their child‚Äôs original birth certificate with the raised seal and immunization record.

Parents who have a child ready to enter the 2020-2021 Preschool class and Hershey Public School and have not received a letter from the school regarding this meeting should notify the elementary office at 308-368-5572.
